---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Projects"
  description="Current projects: Jules AI operational system, personality assessment tools, educational content, and more."
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Projects</h1>

    <div class="project-card">
      <h3><a href="/jules/">Jules</a></h3>
      <span class="status">Live</span>
      <p>
        Open-source AI operational system that runs my business. Content pipelines, research, scheduling, reporting, code. Built on Claude Code with 18 custom skills, 5 hooks, cloud batch automation, and mobile access.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/jules/">How it works &rarr;</a> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules">GitHub &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <h3>Personality Assessments</h3>
      <span class="status">Live</span>
      <p>
        Interactive assessment tools that help people understand themselves better. The first one identifies relationship and communication styles across 9 personality archetypes for adult audiences. React + TypeScript frontend, PHP + MySQL backend. 200+ daily users.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <h3><a href="/articles/">Articles &amp; Content</a></h3>
      <span class="status">Active</span>
      <p>
        Practitioner articles and a subscriber newsletter covering AI automation, solo founding, and building for underserved markets. Published at builtwithjon.com. Built with Astro v6, hosted on Cloudflare.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/articles/">Read the articles &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <h3>What's Next</h3>
      <span class="status">In Development</span>
      <p>
        Expanding the assessment toolkit into new domains. Interest exploration, negotiation frameworks, and personal development assessments for general audiences. Same interactive approach, new areas.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
